OL,6,F"It gives families a moment of
OL,7,Frecognition and a form of reparation.
OL,8,FIt is a moment of reckoning for the
OL,9,Fconvicted."
OL,11,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer
OL,12,Fpromised to carry on the pledge to
OL,13,Fchange the law, first made by his
OL,14,Fpredecessor Rishi Sunak, when he met
OL,15,Fthe mother of murdered nine-year-old
OL,16,FOlivia Pratt-Korbel.
OL,18,FCheryl Korbel and her family have
OL,19,Fcampaigned to change the law so that
OL,20,Foffenders are compelled to appear in
OL,21,Fthe dock for sentencing.
